<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

											EAT-26 (Eating Attitudes Test)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 12-08-2016
last updated:  02-22-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-22-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
This script implements the EAT- 26 (Eating Attitudes Test) as described in:

Garner, D.M., Olmsted, M.P., Boh, Y. & Garfinkle, P.E. (1982). The Eating Attitudes Test: Psychometric features and 
clinical correlates. Psychological Medicine, 12, 871-878

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
26 6-point Likert questions											  

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 3 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'eat26.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	    with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								Note: Scoring:
									q1-q25: always (3). usually (2), often (1) - the remaining answer choices (0)
									q26: reversed coded
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)


(2) Summary data file: 'eat_26_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version: 						Inquisit version run
computer.platform:					the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:							date script was run
startTime:							time script was started
subjectid:							assigned subject id number
groupid:							assigned group id number
sessionid:							assigned session id number
elapsedTime:						time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:							0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
									1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

EAT26_total:						the total score
									Note: Scoring:
									q1-q25: always (3). usually (2), often (1) - the remaining answer choices (0)
									q26: reversed coded
																	
Note:
Norms are calculated based on data published by Garner et al. (1982).
The mean and standard deviation used in this script are derived from a group of female college students (N = 140)
									
zscore:		the z-score of the EAT27 Total Score with mean = 9.9 and sd = 9.2
pvalue:		the percentile of the EAT27 zscore

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
NORMS
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Norms are calculated based on data published by Garner et al. (1982).
The mean and standard deviation used in this script are derived from a group of female college students (N = 140)

Mean = 9.9, SD = 9.2 (see Garner et al., 1982, table 2)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
can be edited under section Editable Parameters

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions-
/pageinstructions2: 	the presented page instructions

Norming Statistics: The mean and standard deviation used in this script are derived from a group of female college students (N = 140) 
(see Garner et al., 1982, table 2)
/mean = 9.9				
/sd = 9.2

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Eating Attitudes Test (EAT-26)
"
/pageinstructions2 = "Please answer the following questions to the best of your abilities. There are no right or wrong answers.
"

/mean = 9.9
/sd = 9.2
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed, 
expressions.EAT26_total, expressions.z_score, expressions.pvalue)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/EAT26_total = radiobuttons.q1.response + radiobuttons.q2.response + radiobuttons.q3.response + radiobuttons.q4.response + 
radiobuttons.q5.response + radiobuttons.q6.response + radiobuttons.q7.response + radiobuttons.q8.response +
radiobuttons.q9.response + radiobuttons.q10.response +
radiobuttons.q11.response + radiobuttons.q12.response + radiobuttons.q13.response + radiobuttons.q14.response + 
radiobuttons.q15.response + radiobuttons.q16.response + radiobuttons.q17.response + radiobuttons.q18.response +
radiobuttons.q19.response + radiobuttons.q20.response + radiobuttons.q21.response +
radiobuttons.q22.response + radiobuttons.q23.response + radiobuttons.q24.response + 
radiobuttons.q25.response + radiobuttons.q26R.response

/z_score = (expressions.EAT26_total - parameters.mean)/parameters.sd
/pvalue = pofz(expressions.z_score)
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "1. Am terrified about being overweight."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "2. Avoid eating when I am hungry."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3>
/caption = "3. Find myself preoccupied with food."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4>
/caption = "4. Have gone on eating binges where I feel that I may not be able to stop."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5>
/caption = "5. Cut my food into small pieces."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6>
/caption = "6. Aware of the calorie content of foods that I eat."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7>
/caption = "7. Particularly avoid food with a high carbohydrate content (i.e. bread, rice, potatoes,etc.)."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8>
/caption = "8. Feel that others would prefer if I ate more."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9>
/caption = "9. Vomit after I have eaten."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10>
/caption = "10. Feel extremely guilty after eating."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11>
/caption = "11. Am preoccupied with a desire to be thinner."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12>
/caption = "12. Think about burning up calories when I exercise."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13>
/caption = "13. Other people think that I am too thin."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q14>
/caption = "14. Am preoccupied with the thought of having fat on my body."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q15>
/caption = "15. Take longer than others to eat my meals."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q16>
/caption = "16. Avoid foods with sugar in them."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q17>
/caption = "17. Eat diet foods."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q18>
/caption = "18. Feel that food controls my life."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q19>
/caption = "19. Display self-control around food."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q20>
/caption = "20. Feel that others pressure me to eat."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q21>
/caption = "21. Give too much time and thought to food."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q22>
/caption = "22. Feel uncomfortable after eating sweets."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q23>
/caption = "23. Engage in dieting behavior."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q24>
/caption = "24. Like my stomach to be empty."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q25>
/caption = "25. Have the impulse to vomit after meals."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0", "0", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q26R>
/caption = "26. Enjoy trying new rich foods."
/ options = ("Always", "Usually", "Often", "Sometimes", "Rarely", "Never")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "0", "0", "1", "2", "3")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage eat26_1>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "<%parameters.pageinstructions2%>"
/questions = [1 = q1, q2, q3]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_2>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q4, q5, q6]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_3>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q7, q8, q9]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_4>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q10, q11, q12]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_5>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/questions = [1 = q13, q14, q15]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_6>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q16, q17, q18]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_7>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q19, q20, q21]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_8>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q22, q23, q24]
</surveypage>

<surveypage eat26_9>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/questions = [1 = q25, q26R]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages
- to take pictures of each screen set /screencapture = true

<survey eat26>
/pages = [
	1 = eat26_1; 
	2 = eat26_2; 
	3 = eat26_3; 
	4 = eat26_4; 
	5 = eat26_5; 
	6 = eat26_6; 
	7 = eat26_7;
	8 = eat26_8;
	9 = eat26_9;
]
/screencapture = false
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 2.0%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = black
/showpagenumbers = false
/showquestionnumbers = false
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>

*******************************************************************************************************************
												End of File
*******************************************************************************************************************